16 paragraph 4"
17 Amend the bill by inserting after section 16 the following:
18 'Sec. 17. Working group; report. The Administrative Office of the Courts shall
19 convene a working group with representatives that are currently employed as bail
20 commissioners to examine the establishment of bail officers, whether bail officers have
21 improved administration of the bail code and whether any further changes to state law are
22 necessary in relation to the establishment of bail officers. The Administrative Office of the
23 Courts shall submit a report containing the findings and recommendations of the working
24 group to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over criminal
25 justice and public safety matters by November 4, 2026. The committee may report out
26 legislation based on the report during the 133rd Legislature in 2027.
27 Sec. 18. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
28 allocations are made.
29 JUDICIAL DEPARTMENT
30 Courts - Supreme, Superior and District 0063
31 Initiative: Provides funding for 3 bail officer positions and related All Other costs to set
32 and execute bail in accordance with the law.
