7 SUMMARY
88 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, amends the bill by
99 retaining a bail commissioner's authority to take the personal recognizance of any
1100 defendant for appearance on a charge of a Class D crime as authorized by current law and
1111 makes a technical change. The amendment requires that the Administrative Office of the
1122 Courts convene a working group with members that are employed as bail commissioners
1133 to examine the establishment of bail officers. The Administrative Office of the Courts shall
1144 submit a report based on the findings of the working group to the joint standing committee
1155 of the Legislature having jurisdiction over criminal justice and public safety matters by
1166 November 4, 2026. The committee may submit legislation based on the report to the 133rd
1177 Legislature in 2027. The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
